How to reset the root Password: (RHEL 10)
-----------------------------------------

-> This method boots directly into a single‑user shell without systemd.

-> Reboot, press 'e' key on the GRUB entry, and on the 'linux' line append:

    init=/bin/bash

-> Press Ctrl+X (or F10) to boot into a bash shell. Remount the root filesystem read‑write:

    # mount -o remount rw /

-> Reset the root password:

    # passwd 

-> SELinux relabel on next boot:

    # touch /.autorelabel

-> Continue the normal boot sequence:

    # exec /sbin/init
